T21	p 4552 5309	According to a study carried out by the CGC itself, which extrapolated the data on the advance of this disease in Florida, the Spanish citrus industry would be reduced by half in 7 years and could disappear in less than 15 if the HLB bacterium finally arrived . Hence, the association now insists on the need for the European Commission to strengthen border controls to the extreme -both with the port inspection of fruits and that of passengers, who can also carry infected plant material- and demands the urgent review of the community strategy regarding synthetic products which, according to the latest proposal for a regulation on the sustainable use of phytosanitary products, would imply their prohibition in large areas devoted to citrus production.
